This paper is about Bayesian deep learning, which involves probabilistic modeling of neural network weights. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on stochastic gradient MCMC, which is a popular method for Bayesian inference in deep learning. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also includes experiments on image classification tasks, indicating relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the proposed method involves a cyclical stepsize schedule, which is a form of optimization, suggesting relevance to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
